<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Lissajous_curve&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<table class="metadata plainlinks mbox-small" style="border:1px solid #aaa; background-color:#f9f9f9;">
<tr>
<td class="mbox-image"><a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:Search/Lissajous_curve" title="commons:Special:Search/Lissajous curve"><img alt="Sister project" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/40px-Commons-logo.svg.png" width="40" height="54" border="0" /></a></td>
<td class="mbox-text" style=""><a href="/wiki/Wikimedia_Commons" title="Wikimedia Commons">Wikimedia Commons</a> has media related to: <b><i><a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Lissajous_Curves" class="extiw" title="commons:Category:Lissajous Curves">Lissajous Curves</a> </i></b></td>
</tr>
</table>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.magnet.fsu.edu/education/tutorials/java/lissajous/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.magnet.fsu.edu/education/tutorials/java/lissajous/index.html" rel="nofollow">Interactive Java Tutorial: Lissajous Figures on Oscilloscope</a> National High Magnetic Field Laboratory</li>
<li><a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/LissajousCurve.html" class="external text" title="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/LissajousCurve.html" rel="nofollow">Lissajous Curve at Mathworld</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece209/lab1_intro/lab1_intro_lissajous.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece209/lab1_intro/lab1_intro_lissajous.pdf" rel="nofollow">ECE 209: Lissajous Figures</a> — a short <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Glossary" title="Wikipedia:Glossary">wikified</a> document that mathematically and graphically explains Lissajous curves for <a href="/wiki/LTI_system_theory" title="LTI system theory">LTI systems</a> and gives an <a href="/wiki/Oscilloscope" title="Oscilloscope">oscilloscope</a> procedure that uses them to find system <a href="/wiki/Phase_(waves)" title="Phase (waves)">phase shift</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://ibiblio.org/e-notes/Lis/Lissa.htm" class="external text" title="http://ibiblio.org/e-notes/Lis/Lissa.htm" rel="nofollow">Animated Lissajous figures in Java</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.abc.net.au/corp/history/hist1.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.abc.net.au/corp/history/hist1.htm" rel="nofollow">About the Australian Broadcasting Corporation logo</a></li>
<li><a href="http://qliss3d.sf.net" class="external text" title="http://qliss3d.sf.net" rel="nofollow">Free tool QLiss3D that displays Lissajous figures in three dimensions</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.carloslabs.com/node/15" class="external text" title="http://www.carloslabs.com/node/15" rel="nofollow">A free Javascript tool for generating Lissajous curves</a></li>
<li><a href="http://geocities.com/Area51/Quadrant/3864/sketchlissajous.htm" class="external text" title="http://geocities.com/Area51/Quadrant/3864/sketchlissajous.htm" rel="nofollow">Lissajous Curves</a>: an interactive applet showing how to trace Lissajous curves in 2D. Requires Java.</li>
<li><a href="http://phy.hk/wiki/englishhtm/Lissajous.htm" class="external text" title="http://phy.hk/wiki/englishhtm/Lissajous.htm" rel="nofollow">A 3D Java applet showing how a Lissajous figure can be traced.</a></li>
<li><a href="http://robertinventor.com/software/Lissajous_3D/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://robertinventor.com/software/Lissajous_3D/index.htm" rel="nofollow">Lissajous 3D</a>: animated textured 3D Lissajous patterns, also Lissajous screen saver for Windows</li>
<li><a href="http://jsxgraph.uni-bayreuth.de/wiki/index.php/Lissajous_curves" class="external free" title="http://jsxgraph.uni-bayreuth.de/wiki/index.php/Lissajous_curves" rel="nofollow">http://jsxgraph.uni-bayreuth.de/wiki/index.php/Lissajous_curves</a>: an interactive JavaScript-applet showing Lissajous curves in 2D. Neither Java nor Flash required, it uses the <a href="http://jsxgraph.org" class="external text" title="http://jsxgraph.org" rel="nofollow">JSXGraph library</a>.</li>
</ul>


